Using property overloading to implement getters/setters in PHP is terrible practice. It's slow, makes the code hard to manage and introduces unexpected behavior.<p><pre><code>      function __set($property, $value){
            if ($property == 'speed'){
               // ...
            }
      }</code></pre>
Just write the damn setter or no setter at all but please don't use property overloading for this!<p><pre><code>     function setSpeed($value) {}</code></pre>
